Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph chapter

Edit chapters inside an existing `.sdpub` archive.

Usage:
  wikigraph chapter list <path> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter status <path> --chapter <id> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter add <path> --stage <planned|source> [--title <title>] [--parent <id>] [--input <path>] [--input-format <format>] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter move <path> --chapter <id> (--parent <id>|--root|--before <id>|--after <id>|--first|--last) [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter remove <path> --chapter <id> [--recursive] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter reset <path> --chapter <id> --to <planned|source|reading-graph> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter set-source <path> --chapter <id> [--input <path>] --input-format <format> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter set-summary <path> --chapter <id> [--input <path>] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter set-title <path> --chapter <id> (--title <title>|--clear) [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter tree <path> [--json] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter tree apply <path> [--input <path>] [--dry-run] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Chapter stages:
  planned     TOC chapter exists, but no source is stored.
  source      Normalized source text is stored.
  reading-graph  Source plus generated Reading Graph are stored.
  reading-summary  Source, Reading Graph, and final summary are stored.

Input rules:
  - `<path>` is the `.sdpub` archive edited in place.
  - `--chapter` is the numeric chapter id printed by `list` or `add`.
  - `add --stage planned` creates an empty planned chapter. Use this for chapter directories, groups, and drafting placeholders.
  - `add --stage source` creates a chapter and fills it from `--input <path>` or stdin.
  - `set-source` and `set-summary` read `--input <path>` when provided, otherwise stdin.
  - `set-source` accepts only `txt` or `markdown` for `--input-format`.
  - `set-title --title` renames a chapter in the tree; `set-title --clear` removes the explicit title.
  - `move` changes parent/order only; it does not edit source, graph, or summary data.
  - `tree` prints the chapter tree as JSON with `title: null` for untitled chapters.
  - `tree apply` applies a complete chapter tree JSON. It can reorder chapters and change titles when a node includes `title`.
  - `reset --to` accepts `planned`, `source`, or `reading-graph`.
  - Structure edits, `set-title`, `set-source`, `set-summary`, and `reset` do not call an LLM provider.
  - To generate reading-graph, reading-summary, or knowledge-graph for a chapter, use `wikigraph queue add <path> --chapter <id> --task <reading-graph|reading-summary|knowledge-graph> --accept-cost`.
  - Append `--help` after an action for action-specific details, for example `wikigraph chapter reset --help`.

